During this course will give the knowledge about the organisation of genetic service in Estonia and their ethical aspects. Thoroughly will be studied different investigation methods in clinical genetics and their interpretation. Separately we will handle the investigation methods of chromosomes, genes and metabolites. Study will focus on most common inherited disorders and/or patient's groups, their diagnostics, counselling and treatment (infertility, familiar cancer, prenatal diagnostics for pregnant women, monogenic and multifactorial disorders, neurogeneterative disorders in adulthood). Finally, we will give the information about the treatment options for inherited disorders and their practical application in Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give detailed overview about all areas of clinical genetics, the diagnostics and treatment of genetic diseases, and the organisation of genetic service in Estonia to the students of Master of Science in biomedicine.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing this study a student of Master of Science in biomedicine knows the basic knowledge of clinical genetics and is prepared to work in cytogenetic, molecular diagnostic and/or in metabolic laboratory.
